BLUETONGUE, BOVINE, OVINE - GERMANY (NORDRHEIN-WESTFALEN): SUSPECTED
***********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: Mon 21 Aug 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Zibb Netherlands, 21 Aug 2006 [translated from Dutch by Mod.AS, edited]
<http://www.zibb.nl/landentuinbouw/nieuwsbericht/asp/artnr/1246248/versie/1/index.html>

Bluetongue near Aachen
---------------------------
Bluetongue disease has been recorded in Germany as well. According to
the authorities of the Duren district, the disease has been confirmed
in sheep and cattle in 3 farms in the vicinity of Aachen. This has
been notified today [21 Aug 2006].
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[Aachen is on the Dutch (Limburg) border, about 12 km south of
(affected) Kerkrade; see map at
<http://www.multimap.com/map/browse.cgi?lat=50.7766&lon=6.0836&scale=500000&icon=x>.
Official confirmation and data on the BTV serotype involved (most
probably identical with the not-yet-published serotype in the
Netherlands and Belgium) are anticipated. - Mod.AS]
